    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-03T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="50"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/8170</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-03T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received</hi> (<hi rend="italic">February 4?</hi>)
                            <hi rend="italic">3 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2567. I am preparing important and long telegram supplementing my 2544, January
                    31, 4 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d50fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_60">p. 60</ref>.</note> I
                    venture to suggest that President withhold any contemplated answer to <persName
                        corresp="#p_CvCCO1">Czernin</persName> until its recepit.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d50fn3">The ensuing telegrams summarizing Professor
                            <persName>Herron</persName>’s account of his conversations with
                            <persName corresp="#p_LH1">Lammasch</persName> are not printed; instead,
                        the complete report rendered by pouch is inserted <hi rend="italic"
                            >post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_82">p. 82</ref>, in the order of date of
                        receipt of the last of the series of telegrams, Feb. 7, 9.43 a.m.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
